'''Judith Reeves-Stevens''' is a [[Wikipedia:Canadians|Canadian]] author who, alongside her husband and co-author [[Garfield Reeves-Stevens]], wrote two ''[[Star Wars]]'' short stories in the 1990s. The pair penned "[[A Bad Feeling: The Tale of EV-9D9]]" for ''[[Tales from Jabba's Palace]]'' and "[[One Last Night in the Mos Eisley Cantina: The Tale of the Wolfman and the Lamproid]]" for ''[[Tales from the Mos Eisley Cantina]]''. They are also well-known for writing numerous books in the [[Wikipedia:Star Trek|''Star Trek'']] franchise, including a [[w:c:memory-alpha:Star_Trek:_The_Original_Series_(Pocket)#Shatnerverse|series]] co-authored by [[Wikipedia:William Shatner|William Shatner]].

